WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.736
(male announcer)
In the criminal justice system,

00:02.770 --> 00:06.540
sexually based offenses are
considered especially heinous.

00:06.574 --> 00:09.377
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:09.410 --> 00:11.179
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:11.212 --> 00:12.680
are members of an elite squad

00:12.713 --> 00:14.415
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:14.448 --> 00:18.086
These are their stories.

00:18.119 --> 00:20.821
[yelling]

00:20.854 --> 00:23.091
(girl)
Kick, punch, elbow, knee.

00:23.124 --> 00:24.558
Kick, punch, elbow, knee...

00:24.592 --> 00:26.327
Is she having a spaz attack?

00:26.360 --> 00:27.728
No, it's Kraft Magoo.

00:27.761 --> 00:30.098
It's Krav Maga,
it's what they teach

00:30.131 --> 00:31.765
secret agents for self-defense.

00:31.799 --> 00:32.733
Where'd you learn it?

00:32.766 --> 00:33.834
My mom.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.337
They do it in her aerobics
class.

00:36.370 --> 00:37.838
Elbow, kick, punch!

00:37.871 --> 00:40.108
[gunshot blares]

00:40.141 --> 00:41.375
What happened?

00:41.409 --> 00:43.111
Everyone inside the school now!

00:43.144 --> 00:44.478
[gunshot]
Oh!

00:44.512 --> 00:45.779
Somebody's got a gun.
Run!

00:45.813 --> 00:48.449
No pushing!
Just keep your heads down!

00:53.587 --> 00:55.789
(male officer)
As far as we know,

00:55.823 --> 00:56.857
shooter's in the wind.

00:56.890 --> 00:58.559
Kids who were hit?

00:58.592 --> 01:00.428
We've covered EMS with
a ballistic blanket.

01:00.461 --> 01:01.762
Pulled one boy
from the playground.

01:01.795 --> 01:04.098
Alive?
No.

01:05.166 --> 01:06.367
Anyone else?

01:06.400 --> 01:08.636
Two hits, both made it
inside the school.

01:08.669 --> 01:09.803
Leg wound's on his way
to Bellevue.

01:09.837 --> 01:12.406
Here comes the other one.

01:12.440 --> 01:13.407
How is she?

01:13.441 --> 01:15.443
GSW to the left shoulder.

01:15.476 --> 01:16.844
Stopped the bleeding
with a pressure dressing.

01:16.877 --> 01:18.712
Vitals are stable.
I'll ride with her.

01:18.746 --> 01:20.281
Hi. What's your name?

01:20.314 --> 01:21.282
Annabelle.

01:21.315 --> 01:22.283
Hi, Annabelle.

01:22.316 --> 01:23.884
Did you see who shot you?

01:23.917 --> 01:25.219
No.

01:25.253 --> 01:27.821
Did anybody threaten you?

01:27.855 --> 01:29.623
Any of your classmates?

01:29.657 --> 01:30.858
No. It hurts.

01:30.891 --> 01:32.160
I know it does, honey,

01:32.193 --> 01:33.827
and you're being very brave.

01:33.861 --> 01:36.864
What did I do?
Why did they shoot me?

01:36.897 --> 01:39.867
I don't know, sweetie.

02:28.282 --> 02:30.251
(Stabler)
How many kids were out there?
42.

02:30.284 --> 02:31.785
It was an hour before
school started.

02:31.819 --> 02:33.421
Most of the students
hadn't arrived yet.

02:33.454 --> 02:34.522
Where was the shooter?

02:34.555 --> 02:35.956
I don't know.
I never saw a gun.

02:35.989 --> 02:37.258
Have there been any threats?

02:37.291 --> 02:38.792
Recently fired employees,
teachers,

02:38.826 --> 02:40.228
disgruntled parents?

02:40.261 --> 02:42.296
We're a public school,
so all of the above.

02:42.330 --> 02:44.765
I'm gonna need a list, okay?

02:44.798 --> 02:46.367
(Cragen)
We're setting up
a family center

02:46.400 --> 02:48.302
at the Fort Tryon Armory.

02:48.336 --> 02:49.903
We'll return the kids
to their parents there,

02:49.937 --> 02:52.940
but I'm gonna need you
to interview 'em first.

02:52.973 --> 02:54.842
(Stabler)
Just tell me everything
you remember

02:54.875 --> 02:56.410
before the gunshots, okay?

02:58.979 --> 03:03.351
Did you hear anyone
saying angry words?

03:04.618 --> 03:07.455
Where did it sound like
the gunshots came from?

03:07.488 --> 03:09.523
Sidewalk.

03:09.557 --> 03:12.393
The sidewalk?

03:12.426 --> 03:14.762
Did you see anyone
on the sidewalk with a gun?

03:14.795 --> 03:15.929
I didn't see the gun.

03:15.963 --> 03:19.300
But I know it wasn't anybody
on the sidewalk.

03:19.333 --> 03:20.601
Well, okay.

03:20.634 --> 03:23.304
Who was it?

03:23.337 --> 03:25.306
I don't know,
but he was in a van.

03:26.774 --> 03:29.009
What was the color of the van?

03:29.042 --> 03:30.978
I didn't see any van.

03:31.011 --> 03:33.514
So what did you see?

03:33.547 --> 03:34.948
Open windows.

03:34.982 --> 03:36.016
From a car?

03:36.049 --> 03:37.818
No, no.
Building windows.

03:37.851 --> 03:40.020
Across the street.

03:40.053 --> 03:41.255
Which building?

03:41.289 --> 03:42.390
All of them.

03:42.423 --> 03:45.426
People were shooting from
all different directions.

03:45.459 --> 03:47.861
So there was more
than one shooter?

03:47.895 --> 03:49.363
No, just one.

03:49.397 --> 03:50.431
He must've been someone
on the playground.

03:50.464 --> 03:53.033
And you're positive you didn't
see who shot you?

03:53.066 --> 03:54.001
Yes.

03:54.034 --> 03:55.403
(male doctor)
Anyone up for good news?

03:55.436 --> 03:56.570
Yeah, I sure am.

03:56.604 --> 03:57.938
X-rays confirm the bullet

03:57.971 --> 04:00.474
completely missed your femur.

04:00.508 --> 04:01.975
You have a little soft tissue
damage,

04:02.009 --> 04:04.645
but you should be back running
marathons in no time.

04:04.678 --> 04:06.980
But I never ran in a marathon.

04:07.014 --> 04:09.750
Well, you will now.

04:09.783 --> 04:12.386
That is how good
we are gonna fix you up.

04:12.420 --> 04:15.022
So, you have no ballistic
evidence for us?

04:15.055 --> 04:17.057
(doctor)
Clean, through and through.

04:17.090 --> 04:18.859
Your bullet is still
on that playground.

04:18.892 --> 04:19.993
Will you make

04:20.027 --> 04:21.595
Jeffrey and Annabelle
all better too?

04:21.629 --> 04:24.332
Dr. Beresford was just
on his way

04:24.365 --> 04:27.335
to check on Annabelle
for us now.

04:27.368 --> 04:29.303
How is she?

04:29.337 --> 04:31.339
Still in surgery.

04:31.372 --> 04:32.706
I'll let you know.

04:32.740 --> 04:34.342
(boy)
Olivia?

04:34.375 --> 04:36.377
I'm right here.

04:36.410 --> 04:37.478
Johnny Mayhew.

04:37.511 --> 04:39.613
Who's that?
He's a boy in my class

04:39.647 --> 04:41.081
that gets a lot of timeouts.

04:41.114 --> 04:42.483
What about him?

04:42.516 --> 04:43.317
He has a gun.

04:43.351 --> 04:46.754
When did you see Johnny
with a gun?

04:46.787 --> 04:49.557
The first day after
summer vacation.

04:49.590 --> 04:51.725
He brought it to school
in his backpack.

04:51.759 --> 04:55.496
He let me hold it.

04:55.529 --> 04:58.832
A .380 semiautomatic
is not a toy, Mrs. Mayhew.

04:58.866 --> 05:00.534
I told you never
to go near that.

05:00.568 --> 05:02.102
Whoa! You're in enough trouble
already.

05:02.135 --> 05:03.103
What'd I do?

05:03.136 --> 05:05.673
This reeks of cleaning oil.

05:05.706 --> 05:08.876
You covering for your son,
Ms. Mayhew?
I clean it once a week.

05:08.909 --> 05:11.044
So it won't jam
if I ever need to use it.

05:11.078 --> 05:14.047
(Munch)
Safety isn't on,
no lock on the drawer.

05:14.081 --> 05:16.750
I guess a child lock
is out of the question, huh?

05:16.784 --> 05:18.986
You got a permit for that?

05:19.019 --> 05:21.021
It was a gift from my brother.

05:21.054 --> 05:22.423
And you never registered it?

05:22.456 --> 05:23.357
I was supposed to?

05:23.391 --> 05:25.493
Mrs. Mayhew, we're gonna
have to charge you

05:25.526 --> 05:26.794
with possession of a weapon

05:26.827 --> 05:28.762
and endangering the welfare
of a child.

05:28.796 --> 05:29.963
Get outta here.

05:29.997 --> 05:33.434
And a tech needs to run a
gunshot residue test on Johnny.

05:33.467 --> 05:35.536
Why? He hadn't even
left the house yet.

05:35.569 --> 05:39.440
There is no way my Johnny
shot those kids.

05:41.809 --> 05:44.412
(man)
A teacher came in early
to grade some math tests.

05:44.445 --> 05:45.913
Was she in here
during the shooting?

05:45.946 --> 05:47.881
Had just gone to the lounge
for coffee.

05:47.915 --> 05:50.718
A stray round came through
this open window,

05:50.751 --> 05:52.486
pierced the map
right there.

05:52.520 --> 05:55.155
Well, it looks like
he took out Tulsa.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.425
Probably unintentional.

05:57.458 --> 06:00.428
And finally came to rest...

06:01.762 --> 06:02.830
right here.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.398
What caliber was the ammo?

06:04.432 --> 06:07.167
Well, they're all too mangled
to tell, but this one

06:07.200 --> 06:09.903
did give us two points
of contact.

06:09.937 --> 06:11.905
The desk...

06:11.939 --> 06:14.442
and the map, which allows us
to ascertain

06:14.475 --> 06:16.143
the exact line of fire.

06:16.176 --> 06:17.878
My left or your left?

06:17.911 --> 06:19.880
Your left.

06:19.913 --> 06:22.416
The shooter picked 'em off
from right here.

06:22.450 --> 06:23.584
Got something.

06:23.617 --> 06:25.185
Cozy little sniper's nest.

06:25.218 --> 06:26.787
Perfect location.

06:26.820 --> 06:29.189
Complete with
a little hiding place.

06:29.222 --> 06:30.357
What'd he leave us?

06:30.390 --> 06:33.694
It looks like he was smart
enough to pick up his brass.

06:33.727 --> 06:36.730
But remember that line, "Leave
the gun, take the cannoli"?

06:36.764 --> 06:39.199
That explains why no one
saw a weapon afterwards.

06:39.232 --> 06:41.168
Folding stock,

06:41.201 --> 06:43.103
bolt action, internal magazine.

06:43.136 --> 06:45.205
High-powered scope
and a flash suppressor.

06:45.238 --> 06:47.541
I think we can rule out
little Johnny Mayhew.

06:47.575 --> 06:48.175
This is a precision

06:48.208 --> 06:49.710
sniper rifle.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.212
Kind you use with
a specific target in mind.

06:52.245 --> 06:54.915
Which kid was he gunning for?

06:58.886 --> 07:00.888
(Benson)
Can you think of any reason

07:00.921 --> 07:02.456
that somebody may have
targeted your daughter?

07:02.490 --> 07:03.591
Of course not.

07:03.624 --> 07:05.893
What reason could anybody have
to shoot a six-year-old?

07:05.926 --> 07:08.462
What about you?
Have you had any threats?

07:08.496 --> 07:09.897
Any recent disputes?
No.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.799
We just moved here
from Denver last month.

07:11.832 --> 07:13.467
We hardly know anyone.

07:13.501 --> 07:15.869
Detective, you wanted
to be told.

07:15.903 --> 07:19.640
The boy who didn't make it,
his mother just got here.

07:23.043 --> 07:24.778
Mrs. Whitlock.

07:24.812 --> 07:26.547
I'm Detective Benson.

07:26.580 --> 07:29.517
Uh, yes, I got a message that my
son Jeffrey was hurt at school.

07:29.550 --> 07:32.152
And to come here.
Is--is he okay?

07:32.185 --> 07:34.021
I don't understand why
they won't let me see him.

07:34.054 --> 07:37.257
No one's talked to you.
No. W-w-what happened?

07:37.290 --> 07:39.026
W-where is he?

07:39.059 --> 07:40.528
You know what, why don't we
have a seat right over here--

07:40.561 --> 07:42.029
No, no, no, I-I need to be
with my son.

07:42.062 --> 07:44.532
My husband can't have
his cell phone on at work, and--

07:44.565 --> 07:47.501
Only I guess that's what we gave
the emergency contact number

07:47.535 --> 07:49.603
to the school, and h-he picked
it up on break,

07:49.637 --> 07:51.605
and he left a message for me
at home that I--that I--

07:51.639 --> 07:54.542
that I should meet him here,
but he--he didn't--

08:00.548 --> 08:02.616
Mrs. Whitlock.

08:02.650 --> 08:05.252
I'm so sorry.

08:05.285 --> 08:08.288
Please...don't...

08:08.321 --> 08:11.625
There was a shooting
at the school.

08:11.659 --> 08:13.994
Your son didn't make it.

08:18.666 --> 08:21.902
Oh, God!

08:29.577 --> 08:32.512
My husband's here.

08:33.781 --> 08:37.017
I don't know how
I'm gonna tell him.

08:37.050 --> 08:39.152
You're a corrections officer?

08:39.186 --> 08:42.122
Rikers.

08:45.358 --> 08:48.061
[sobbing]
Oh, God!

08:50.831 --> 08:54.935
[sobbing]
Oh...

09:00.874 --> 09:02.776
Your son Jeffrey was...
Adopted.

09:02.810 --> 09:03.977
A year ago.

09:04.011 --> 09:06.714
We couldn't
get pregnant.

09:06.747 --> 09:09.282
They said the wait list
to adopt was years.

09:09.316 --> 09:13.053
Unless you happened to be rich.
Which we're not.

09:13.086 --> 09:17.357
And then we found out there were
20,000 kids in foster care.

09:17.390 --> 09:18.525
Just in New York City.

09:18.558 --> 09:22.730
They said 5,000 were legally
free to adopt, immediately.

09:22.763 --> 09:26.700
Jeffrey was in the
harder-to-place older group.

09:26.734 --> 09:28.669
Kids over seven.

09:28.702 --> 09:29.837
Mark works at Rikers.

09:29.870 --> 09:32.339
Every day he has to deal
with the end results

09:32.372 --> 09:35.342
of ruined childhoods.

09:35.375 --> 09:38.045
Circle of violence.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.614
We thought we were saving him.

09:40.648 --> 09:43.316
Mr. Whitlock, we have to
consider an inmate at Rikers

09:43.350 --> 09:45.653
with a grudge.

09:45.686 --> 09:48.622
We house 17,000 cons there.

09:49.957 --> 09:52.893
Anybody stick out?

09:52.926 --> 09:55.162
I've been spit at, swung at.

09:55.195 --> 09:58.632
I had food, urine, even feces
thrown at me.

09:58.666 --> 10:02.903
I've had my share of threats,
but so has every guard there.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.138
How could they know
who Jeffrey was?

10:05.172 --> 10:08.075
Why take it out on him?

10:08.108 --> 10:11.311
He was so sweet.

10:11.344 --> 10:14.815
I can't believe he's gone.

10:18.952 --> 10:20.988
(Cragen)
You're all going to be reunited
with your children.

10:21.021 --> 10:22.956
The counselors are available
inside.

10:22.990 --> 10:25.358
So please, let your kids
talk to them.

10:25.392 --> 10:27.394
Maddy, thanks for your help,
darling.

10:27.427 --> 10:30.230
Captain, I think
that's about it.

10:30.263 --> 10:31.999
Kids give you anything?

10:32.032 --> 10:33.901
Yeah, about 40 different
versions about what happened.

10:33.934 --> 10:36.303
Well, eyewitness accounts
are bad enough with adults,

10:36.336 --> 10:37.738
what'd you expect from kids?

10:37.771 --> 10:39.206
Wild imaginations,
high suggestibility,

10:39.239 --> 10:41.942
and difficulty distinguishing
fantasy from reality.

10:41.975 --> 10:43.310
That's pretty much
what I got.

10:43.343 --> 10:45.312
Well, we got a dad
of the one fatality

10:45.345 --> 10:47.781
who's a corrections officer
at Rikers.
Really?

10:47.815 --> 10:49.717
(Maddy)
No! I don't want to go home!

10:49.750 --> 10:51.051
Maddy, come on.

10:51.084 --> 10:52.252
Come on, honey.

10:52.285 --> 10:53.721
I interviewed her, nothing.

10:53.754 --> 10:55.723
Well, we'd better
re-interview her.

10:55.756 --> 10:57.758
Come on.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.793
(Huang)
Maddy, where do you live?

10:59.827 --> 11:02.462
In an apartment.

11:02.495 --> 11:04.998
Does anyone live
in the apartment with you?

11:05.032 --> 11:06.299
Yes.
Who?

11:06.333 --> 11:07.701
My mom.

11:07.735 --> 11:12.005
Anyone else?
No.

11:12.039 --> 11:14.708
Maddy, is anyone ever...

11:14.742 --> 11:16.176
mean to you?

11:16.209 --> 11:18.345
Yes.

11:18.378 --> 11:20.280
Who?

11:20.313 --> 11:23.216
I promised not to tell.

11:23.250 --> 11:25.986
What would happen if you told?

11:26.019 --> 11:28.155
He has a giant gun,
as tall as me,

11:28.188 --> 11:29.857
and he said if I told,

11:29.890 --> 11:32.893
he'd shoot my mom
and all my friends.

11:32.926 --> 11:35.228
Maddy, who is he?

11:35.262 --> 11:36.830
If I go home,

11:36.864 --> 11:39.867
he'll shoot me too because
he'll think I told.

11:39.900 --> 11:42.102
But I swear I didn't tell.

11:42.135 --> 11:45.205
What does he do to hurt you?

11:48.208 --> 11:51.812
He makes me pull down my pants.

11:51.845 --> 11:54.982
Please don't let him
shoot my mom.

11:56.216 --> 11:59.186
We won't let him
hurt anybody else.

11:59.219 --> 12:02.255
But you gotta tell me
who he is first, okay?

12:06.794 --> 12:09.462
Maddy.

12:09.496 --> 12:11.899
Who is he?

12:11.932 --> 12:13.901
Mr. Bugeyes.

12:13.934 --> 12:16.003
(woman)
She means Mr. Buggesi.

12:16.036 --> 12:17.838
She has trouble
pronouncing his name.

12:17.871 --> 12:18.772
And who's Mr. Buggesi?

12:18.806 --> 12:21.008
He's an elderly gentleman
in our building.

12:21.041 --> 12:22.509
Retired, he's very friendly.

12:22.542 --> 12:24.344
How often is Maddy
alone with him?

12:26.046 --> 12:27.981
Did he do something to her?

12:28.015 --> 12:30.984
Well, we just need
to speak with him.

12:31.018 --> 12:32.986
Maddy gets out of school
at 3:00,

12:33.020 --> 12:35.222
but I don't get off work
until 5:00.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.991
He says he likes
to keep himself useful.

12:38.025 --> 12:39.927
He watches her for free.

12:39.960 --> 12:42.395
Which apartment is he in?

12:44.932 --> 12:46.233
(man)
Don't! stop!

12:46.266 --> 12:47.434
(man 2)
Do you like that?

12:47.467 --> 12:50.070
Mr. Buggesi?

12:50.103 --> 12:53.273
Mr. Buggesi, open the door!

12:53.306 --> 12:54.975
(man)
You raped your last
little girl,

12:55.008 --> 12:57.244
you rancid bag of puss!
(Cragen)
Hey! Hey!

12:57.277 --> 12:58.912
All right, enough, enough,
enough, enough!

12:58.946 --> 13:00.914
Let go!
Get over here.
Get over here.

13:00.948 --> 13:02.049
Get over here.
Hands against the wall.

13:02.082 --> 13:03.583
Hands against the wall.

13:03.616 --> 13:04.818
He's unconscious.

13:04.852 --> 13:06.119
(Stabler)
Who are you?

13:06.153 --> 13:07.855
SVU Portable to Central.

13:07.888 --> 13:09.589
I need a bus for an aided
prisoner at 54th and 2nd.

13:09.622 --> 13:12.125
Apartment 4-C as in Charlie.

13:12.159 --> 13:13.827
10-4, bus is on the way.

13:13.861 --> 13:15.428
Patrick McCorkle.

13:15.462 --> 13:17.130
Any relation to Maddy?

13:17.164 --> 13:17.998
My niece.

13:18.031 --> 13:19.266
(Stabler)
Looks like Mrs. McCorkle

13:19.299 --> 13:20.467
gave Patrick here the heads-up.

13:20.500 --> 13:21.468
Now, look,

13:21.501 --> 13:23.103
I understand you're very angry.

13:23.136 --> 13:24.304
I don't think you do.

13:24.337 --> 13:26.006
We're still arresting you.
Fine.

13:26.039 --> 13:27.474
Just put us in the same cell.

13:27.507 --> 13:30.177
Buggesi say anything to you
before you scrambled his brains?

13:30.210 --> 13:31.945
He said he was sorry.

13:31.979 --> 13:33.480
That he was born
with unnatural urges,

13:33.513 --> 13:35.548
he couldn't control himself.

13:38.618 --> 13:40.287
Look at this.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.989
That's what
he threatened her with?

13:42.022 --> 13:43.523
It's an air pellet rifle.

13:43.556 --> 13:46.093
A toy.

13:48.095 --> 13:49.897
Looks as real
as a sniper rifle.

13:49.930 --> 13:51.131
Especially to
a seven-real-old.

13:51.164 --> 13:53.200
Yeah, except this one didn't
take out three kids

13:53.233 --> 13:55.135
on that playground.

