Excuse me.
And you take care.

37:52.037 --> 37:55.040
Detective Tutuola,
I want to apologize to you for--

37:55.073 --> 37:56.842
We're good.

37:56.875 --> 37:58.577
All right.
Take care.

38:00.979 --> 38:02.814
So where is it you got shot?

38:02.848 --> 38:04.015
That would be in the ass.

38:04.049 --> 38:05.917
You want to kiss it
and make it better?

38:05.951 --> 38:06.985
You be nice to me

38:07.018 --> 38:09.955
or you won't get the shake
I smuggled in for you.

38:09.988 --> 38:11.423
Fig? From McClinty's?

38:11.457 --> 38:12.824
Of course.
Oh, thanks, man.

38:12.858 --> 38:13.992
Thank you for not making me

38:14.025 --> 38:16.628
have to break in
another partner.

38:16.662 --> 38:19.998
I'm glad you pulled through,
bro.

38:20.031 --> 38:22.668
Did anyone call Kathy yet?
No. Don't.

38:22.701 --> 38:24.903
Eliot.
Don't be like that--

38:24.936 --> 38:27.673
She started divorce proceedings.

38:27.706 --> 38:29.375
When?

38:29.408 --> 38:31.810
A couple weeks ago.

38:31.843 --> 38:35.881
I have the papers at home,
I just haven't signed 'em yet.

38:38.116 --> 38:39.818
How'd they get the guns in?

38:39.851 --> 38:43.489
Uh, Christopher Rawlings
was the adult shooter.

38:43.522 --> 38:45.691
He's a member of RAW,
he had a fake badge and I.D.

38:45.724 --> 38:47.693
Don't have to go through
the metal detector.

38:47.726 --> 38:48.560
They waved him right around.

38:48.594 --> 38:50.429
Handed off the gun
to Kyle Ackerman.

38:50.462 --> 38:52.130
Any casualties?

38:52.163 --> 38:54.966
One of the court officers
is still touch and go.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.134
The other one didn't make it.

38:56.167 --> 38:59.671
And, uh, neither
did Judge Schuyler.

39:01.907 --> 39:03.709
You talk with Brian Ackerman?

39:03.742 --> 39:05.377
He said that he was

39:05.411 --> 39:08.414
proud that his son Kyle
died a hero.

39:08.447 --> 39:10.582
Fighting for his race.

39:18.123 --> 39:21.159
Hey, Ms. Benson.
Our sting went down.

39:21.192 --> 39:23.094
What'd you get?

39:23.128 --> 39:25.564
Two prime targets purchasing
about 50 pounds

39:25.597 --> 39:26.832
of ammonium nitrate, urea,

39:26.865 --> 39:29.401
and a bunch of other fixin's
for a bomb.

39:29.435 --> 39:31.770
It's an exact replica of the one
McVeigh used in Oklahoma City.

39:31.803 --> 39:33.104
What was the target?

39:33.138 --> 39:35.106
We don't know.

39:35.140 --> 39:37.776
Well, at least you got 'em.

39:37.809 --> 39:40.479
You're gonna like this.

39:40.512 --> 39:41.680
During the subsequent raid,

39:41.713 --> 39:45.751
we found some information that
may be pertinent to your case.

39:50.456 --> 39:52.458
(Benson)
There are no pictures
of Jeffrey.

39:52.491 --> 39:58.029
Jana's had a hard time
dealing with his death.

39:58.063 --> 40:01.533
Counselor recommended
removing all reminders.

40:01.567 --> 40:04.069
She must've kept
some little keepsake.

40:04.102 --> 40:08.574
A school project,
a favorite toy?

40:08.607 --> 40:10.108
What is this about?

40:10.141 --> 40:13.178
This is about just how precious
your son was to you.

40:13.211 --> 40:15.481
According to the two
insurance policies

40:15.514 --> 40:16.948
that you took out on him,

40:16.982 --> 40:19.217
Jeffrey was worth exactly

40:19.250 --> 40:20.719
$750,000.

40:20.752 --> 40:22.187
What?

40:22.220 --> 40:23.889
(Lewis)
A bit excessive.
Don't you think?

40:23.922 --> 40:24.723
I mean, considering

40:24.756 --> 40:26.658
that the average
life insurance policy

40:26.692 --> 40:29.461
on a child is only $50,000.

40:29.495 --> 40:31.129
It's what our insurance broker
recommended.

40:31.162 --> 40:32.130
(Benson)
And you had no problem

40:32.163 --> 40:34.766
paying the $350 a month premium?

40:34.800 --> 40:35.767
(Lewis)
I think you would.

40:35.801 --> 40:37.469
Seeing as how you filed

40:37.503 --> 40:39.471
for bankruptcy
only two years ago.

40:39.505 --> 40:41.640
You don't have to rich to give
a child a home.

40:41.673 --> 40:44.943
(Benson)
You filed the insurance claim
five days after Jeffrey died.

40:44.976 --> 40:47.779
You couldn't wait, could ya?

40:50.281 --> 40:51.983
This is insane.

40:54.285 --> 40:57.255
These were obtained
from an FBI raid

40:57.288 --> 40:58.924
of a skinhead terrorist group.

40:58.957 --> 41:00.992
You were mentioned by name,
Mr. Whitlock.

41:01.026 --> 41:03.128
(Benson)
It shows the amount
that you pledged them

41:03.161 --> 41:07.232
from a future
insurance payment.

41:07.265 --> 41:11.202
Somebody's setting me up.

41:11.236 --> 41:13.171
One-third of $750,000.

41:13.204 --> 41:15.206
How would they know
the exact amount

41:15.240 --> 41:17.275
of your combined policies?

41:17.308 --> 41:19.545
(Benson)
Brannon didn't get your son's
picture from Ackerman.

41:19.578 --> 41:20.912
You're the one

41:20.946 --> 41:23.114
who provided them
with Jeffrey's school picture.

41:27.819 --> 41:30.221
You two adopted
this beautiful child

41:30.255 --> 41:32.190
just to kill him, didn't you?

41:33.258 --> 41:34.760
You don't understand--

41:34.793 --> 41:36.828
(Benson)
People must've been surprised
that knew you.

41:36.862 --> 41:40.966
Two racists like you
adopting a little black boy?

41:46.605 --> 41:49.107
We're not racists.

41:49.140 --> 41:52.177
We just needed the money.

41:54.780 --> 41:54.846
